description:
Liven up your video calls with p5.js, ml5.js, Teachable Machine, and OBS Studio!
💻 Code: https://thecodingtrain.com/CodingChallenges/157-zoom-annotations.html

Links discussed in this video:
🔗 Comic-Book Style Video Lens: https://twitter.com/cameronhunter/status/1305667539922550784
🔗 Snap Lens Studio: https://lensstudio.snapchat.com/
🔗 Teachable Machine Website: https://teachablemachine.withgoogle.com/
🔗 ml5.js Teachable Machine Example: https://editor.p5js.org/ml5/sketches/ImageModel_TM
🔗 OBS Studio Website: https://obsproject.com/
🔗 OBS Virtual Cam for Mac: https://github.com/johnboiles/obs-mac-virtualcam/releases
🔗 obs-v4l2sink (OBS Virtual Cam for Linux): https://github.com/CatxFish/obs-v4l2sink

Other videos mentioned in this video:
🎥 Teachable Machine 1: Image Classification: https://youtu.be/kwcillcWOg0

0:00 Introduction
1:02 Project overview and plan
3:43 Teachable Machine model training: https://teachablemachine.withgoogle.com/
5:58 Code! Importing the model: https://editor.p5js.org/ml5/sketches/ImageModel_TM
7:08 Code! Displaying annotations
8:58 Code! Debouncing, fading out
11:20 Open Broadcast Studio Virtual Camera
14:33 Finalizing layout in OBS for Zoom
18:14 Reviewing all the steps
19:47 Further ideas and how to share your own!
